Irate youths on Thursday evening, attacked the convoy of Borno State governor, Babagana Zulum, in Kaleri community, Maiduguri, the State capital. The attackers destroyed three vehicles in the convoy. A report by Zagazola Makama, a counter insurgency expert in the Lake Chad region said the governor was returning from Mafa, his hometown when the attack occurred. Sources told Makama that a vehicles conveying the press crew, the engineers as well as one other were smashed. Few days ago, irate youths attacked campaign convoy of the governorâ€™s wife, Hajiya Falmata Zulum in the axis of Dalori, in Konduga. Eight vehicles were destroyed during the attack.